 you banned.  <br><br>So, if you accidentally dupe something, petition a GM immediately.  You want to make sure that the petition goes out before the GM contacts you to ban your butt.  That way, if a GM says to you, &quot;Hi, I believe you have been duping stuff.  You are in serious trouble.&quot;, you can just reply, &quot;Check the petitions.  I already reported it.&quot;<br><br>If you feel you must test a duping bug to see if it is reproducible, test it with something trivial like bandages or a fine steel weapon or something similarly worthless.  If a GM catches you with five CoF's, he is much less likely to buy the, &quot;I was just testing it for reproducibility.&quot; excuse.<br><br>If you read about a dupe-method on the internet and decide to try it out, don't.  Odds are good that by the time you hear about it on the internet Verant has heard about it as well.  It is possible that they will run more frequent dupe checks until they figure out how to patch the dupe bug out of existence (increasing the odds of you getting caught, even if you destroy all the duped items after you dupe them).  They may also install some sort of &quot;alarm&quot; that goes off when someone does the things necessary for duping.<br><br>Lag can on VERY rare occasions lead to the duplication of an item.  It is much more likely to result in the loss of the item than its duplication.  <br><br>I debated with myself whether or not to include info on how some people have duped stuff in the past (methods that no longer work), but decided not to, lest someone try them and get themselves banned.<br><br>One more thing.  There are scams out there that involve people pretending to know how to dupe stuff.  NEVER trust anyone that says they can dupe one of your nice items.  They will simply take it and keep it.  In some cases, they may have enough of the same items that you have that they can pretend to dupe an item of yours to prove they can do it, when they actually already had an item like yours.  They show you both items and make you think they know how to dupe stuff, when they don't, so you will then give them a very nice item plus some cash for them to dupe the item.  Then they will camp out.  What are you going to do about it?  Will you complain to the GM's that the guy didn't dupe your item like he said he would?  After they get through laughing, they will ban you.<br> <p>Argfeld<BR>Level 57 Monk of the Celestial Fists<BR>Order of the Scattered Winds<BR>Bertoxxulous<BR><BR>"The secret to being a great monk is to train constantly." . . . Argfeld<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucurscale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>curscale</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 366<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/2/02 1:37:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://thumb-1.image.altavista.com/image/15837144 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Check it out 8k outa nothing courtesy of the bazaar</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Psst... guys... the Mysterious Monk has two posts. I think it's safe to say he's not entirely truthful. As far as I know, during a lag spike, you're more likely to lose your items and come up with nothing than combine them<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>His only other post was in the guides and tactics section where he only made 4k =P, that thread was already removed as im sure this one will be as well. Just some nob trying to mess with people. <p><img src=http://newbie.tscentral.net/images/TalkingAbout.jpg><br><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=140534">My Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc>